üåç International Human Rights Day reminds us that equality isn‚Äôt optional, it‚Äôs a human right.

Observed every year on December 10, this day marks the anniversary of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights (UDHR), adopted by the United Nations in 1948. It was the first global statement to affirm that every person is born free and equal in dignity and rights, regardless of who they are or whom they love.

üè≥Ô∏è‚Äçüåà Today, as LGBTQIA+ communities continue to face discrimination, violence, legislative rollbacks, and efforts to restrict visibility and bodily autonomy, this reminder is more urgent than ever. Human rights protections must include gender identity, sexual orientation, access to healthcare, safety, and the freedom to live authentically.

At IMPAQT GSO, we believe that advancing LGBTQIA+ rights is inseparable from advancing human rights. Our community is stronger together, and together we continue the fight for equity, dignity, and justice.

‚ú® Equality is a human right, for ALL of us.

Today is World AIDS Day.
A day to honor the lives we‚Äôve lost, uplift those living with HIV, and recommit to the work that‚Äôs still unfinished.

In a political climate where public health funding, LGBTQIA+ rights, and access to essential care are increasingly under attack, HIV awareness and prevention matter more than ever. Stigma is still costing lives. Misinformation is still spreading faster than the truth. And many in our community still face barriers to testing, treatment, and support simply for being who they are.

But we know this:
HIV is preventable. HIV is treatable. Undetectable = Untransmittable.
And everyone deserves access to the care, dignity, and community they need to thrive.

‚ú® Free and confidential HIV & STI testing
‚ú® Access to PrEP/PEP
‚ú® Support for people living with HIV
‚ú® Education rooted in facts, not fear

Today, we remember.
Today, we fight stigma.
Today, we call for equitable access to healthcare‚Äîbecause our community‚Äôs rights, health, and lives are not up for debate.

Spread the awareness. Spread the truth. Spread compassion.

#WorldAIDSDay #IMPAQTGSO
